    20. Protocol Documentation

    20.1 genAccelleran5GTypes.proto

    20.1.1 E1LinkPolicy

    Groups parameters that define the policy relating to the use of E1 links.

    Field Type Label Description
    SctpPolicy SctpPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy for the use of SCTP on E1 links.

    20.1.2 F1CLinkPolicy

    Groups parameters that define the policy relating to the use of F1-c links.

    Field Type Label Description
    SctpPolicy SctpPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy for the use of SCTP on F1-c links.

    20.1.3 NgCLinkPolicy

    Groups parameters that define the policy relating to the use of NG-C links.

    Field Type Label Description
    SctpPolicy SctpPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy for the use of SCTP on NG-C links.

    20.1.4 NrCellGlobalIdentity

    Field Type Label Description
    PlmnIdentity string optional
    NrCellIdentity uint64 optional

    20.1.5 ReportPollingConfig

    Field Type Label Description
    TimerEnabled bool optional
    PduWithoutPollCountEnabled bool optional
    Timer uint32 optional
    NumPduWithoutPoll uint32 optional

    20.1.6 SNssai

    Field Type Label Description
    Sst Sst optional Slice/Service Type.
    Sd uint32 optional Slice Differentiator.

    20.1.7 SctpPolicy

    Field Type Label Description
    InStreams uint32 optional The maximum number of inbound streams that will be accepted.
    OutStreams uint32 optional The number of outbound streams that will be requested.

    20.1.8 SsbMtc

    Field Type Label Description
    SmtcPeriodicity SsbMtcPeriodicity optional
    SmtcOffset uint32 optional SSB transmission offset in subframes
    Duration uint32 optional

    20.1.9 SupportedPlmnSlices

    Groups information about a PLMN and the set of slices supported by that PLMN.

    20.14.28 RegistrationRequestObject

    Field Type Label Description
    UserId string optional The UR-ID per [n.12] R2-SRR-02 conformant per section 2.2 of [n.18].
    FccId string optional The FCC certification identifier of the CBSD. It is a string of up to 19 characters as described in [n.22]
    CbsdSerialNumber string optional A serial number assigned to the CBSD by the CBSD device manufacturer having a maximum length of 64 octets. This serial number shall be unique for every CBSD instance sharing the same value of fccId. Each CBSD has a single CBSD Antenna (Ref. definition in section 4) and has a single cbsdSerialNumber.
    CallSign string optional A device identifier provided by the FCC per [n.13].
    CbsdCategory CbsdCategory optional Device Category of the CBSD. Allowed values are 'A' or 'B' as defined in Part 96
    CbsdInfo CbsdInfo optional Information about this CBSD model.
    AirInterface AirInterfaceObject optional A data object that includes information on the air interface technology of the CBSD.
    InstallationParam InstallationParamObject optional A data object that includes information on CBSD installation.
    MeasurementCapabilities MeasurementCapabilitiesObject optional The array of string lists measurement reporting capabilities of the CBSD. The permitted enumerations are specified in [n.21].
    GroupingParam GroupingParam optional An array of data objects that includes information on CBSD grouping.
    CpiSignatureData CpiSignatureData optional The CPI is vouching for the parameters included in this object. In addition, the digital signature for these parameters is included.

    LeafName string optional
    Operation Operation optional
    Origin Origin optional

    20.37.3 XpathList

    Field Type Label Description
    items XpathItem repeated Carries max MAX_NUM_OF_XPATHS elements of type XpathItem

    20.37.4 FilterModeType

    Specifies how you want filterinf done

    Name Number Description
    Filter_PREFIX 0 If the XPATH matches the beginning the filter will pass
    Filter_FULL 1 The XPATH must match exactly in order to pass
    Filter_LEAF 2 The XPATH must match exactly and the leaf must be matching in order to pass
    Filter_PREFIX_IGNORE_KEYS 3 If the XPATH matches the beginning the filter will pass (after the path was cleaned of keys attributes)
    Filter_FULL_IGNORE_KEYS 4 The XPATH must match exactly in order to pass (after the path was cleaned of keys attributes)
    Filter_LEAF_IGNORE_KEYS 5 The XPATH must match exactly and the leaf must be matching in order to pass (after the path was cleaned of keys attributes)

    20.37.5 Operation

    Specifies what happend (Create Update Delete)

    Name Number Description
    Operation_UNKNOWN 0 The operation could not be determined
    Operation_CREATE 1 A create was done for the given xpath/leaf
    Operation_UPDATE 2 An update was done for the given xpath/leaf
    Operation_DELETE 3 A delete was done for the given xpath/leaf
    Operation_ALL 4 value to indicate that all operations are good

    20.37.6 Origin

    Specifies where the modification came from

    Name Number Description
    Origin_APP 0 Modification was done by the application
    Origin_NETCONF 1 Modification was done via NetConf

    20.73 genGNBCUCPTypes.proto

    20.73.1 AdmissionControl

    Contains the configuration for RIC based UE/PDU session admission control

    Field Type Label Description
    RicUeAdmissionControlEnabled bool optional Send a message to the RIC to ask it for permission to admit a UE and wait for the response
    RicPduAdmissionControlEnabled bool optional Send a message to the RIC to ask it for permission to admit a PDU and wait for the response

    20.73.2 GnbCuCp

    Grouping for the class representing a gNB-CU-CP.

    Field Type Label Description
    GnbId uint32 optional The gNB ID part of the Global gNB ID.
    PlmnId string optional 5 or 6 digit PLMN code (MCC and MNC) of the PLMN to which the gNB belongs. Forms part of the gNB's Global gNB ID as used in NGAP messages.
    GnbIdLength uint32 optional The length of the bit string representation of the gNB ID.
    GnbCuCpName string optional Human readable name of the gNB-CU-CP. If configured, this is sent to a gNB-CU-UP, gNB-DU and AMF during the E1, F1 and NG Setup procedures respectively.
    AdminState PBAccGenTypes.AdminState optional Administrative state. Value 'unlocked' means that the gNB is permitted to serve users. Value 'locked' means that the gNB is prohibited from serving users. In the 'locked' state, all of the gNB's cells will be off air.
    RlcMode PBAcc5GTypes.RlcMode optional Contains RLC mode entity value.
    OpState PBAccGenTypes.OpState optional Operational state. Value 'disabled' means that the gNB is totally inoperable and unable to provide service to users. Value 'enabled' means that the gNB is partially or fully operable and available for use.
    NbrOfAllowedCipheringAlgorithm uint32 optional automatically added field for "allowed-ciphering-algorithm" list
    AllowedCipheringAlgorithm PBAcc5GTypes.CipheringAlgorithm repeated List of 5G ciphering algorithms allowed to be used in the gNB, in decreasing order of preference, i.e. most preferred algorithm first. If nea0 is included, it should be the last entry in the list. Ciphering algorithms that are not supported by the gNB must not be included in the list.
    NbrOfAllowedIntegrityAlgorithm uint32 optional automatically added field for "allowed-integrity-algorithm" list
    AllowedIntegrityAlgorithm PBAcc5GTypes.IntegrityAlgorithm repeated List of 5G integrity algorithms allowed to be used in the gNB, in decreasing order of preference, i.e. most preferred algorithm first. nia0 should only be included in deployments where support of unauthenticated emergency calling is a regulatory requirement, and should be the last entry in the list. Integrity algorithms that are not supported by the gNB must not be included in the list.
    E1LinkPolicy PBAcc5GTypes.E1LinkPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy relating to the use of SCTP on E1 interfaces.
    F1CLinkPolicy PBAcc5GTypes.F1CLinkPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy relating to the use of SCTP on F1-c interfaces.
    NbrOfOperator uint32 optional automatically added field for "operator" list
    Operator Operator repeated Data relating to an operator who makes use of the gNB's services and resources. There may be more than one operator in the case of RAN sharing.

    20.73.3 HandoverControl

    Contains the configuration for RSRP triggered A3 events used for handover control

    Field Type Label Description
    Enabled bool optional Controls if the gNB-CU-CP configures measurement reports for handover and triggers handovers based on them. This does not affect the ability to trigger handover through external handover commands.

    20.73.4 NgCLink

    Grouping for the class representing an NG-C link.

    Field Type Label Description
    DestAddress string optional IP address or FQDN of the AMF at the far end of the link.
    OpState PBAccGenTypes.OpState optional Value 'enabled' means that an SCTP association has been established and an NG Setup procedure has been successfully performed with the AMF at the far end of the link; otherwise the value is 'disabled'.
    DefaultAmf bool optional Corresponds to default AMF as specified in [3GPP 23.501]
    AmfName string optional This is the value of the AMF Name received in an NGAP message from the AMF at the far end of the link.

    20.74 genGNBCUUPTypes.proto

    20.74.1 GnbCuUp

    Represents a gNB-CU-UP.

    Field Type Label Description
    UpIntegrityProtectionEnabled bool optional Value true means that the CU-UP will activate integrity protection of DRBs if requested, subject to the specified integrity algorithm being supported; false means that it will not activate integrity protection of DRBs under any circumstances. This determines how the CU-UP handles receipt of a Security Indication IE with the Integrity Protection Indication IE set to 'required' or 'preferred', over E1.
    UpCipheringEnabled bool optional Value true means that the CU-UP will activate confidentiality protection of DRBs if requested, subject to the specified ciphering algorithm being supported; false means that it will not activate confidentiality protection of DRBs under any circumstances. This determines how the CU-UP handles receipt of a Security Indication IE with the Confidentiality Protection Indication IE set to 'required' or 'preferred', over E1.

    20.118.11 VarSizeContainerWithComplexType

    A var sized container is only defined in yang files for messaging ads they are not known to the datastore. This structure mimics the fact that a var sized container can use complex types from different modules. Also note the cardinality. This can now be rediculously big as we do not longer have arrays to store the data but vectors

    Field Type Label Description
    items PBTGTT.RemoteService repeated Carries max 60000 elements of type PBTGTT.RemoteService

    20.118.12 VarSizeContainerWithDeferredType

    A var sized container is only defined in yang files for messaging as they are not known to the datastore. This structure mimics the fact that a var sized container can use types that were defined in different modules and annotated by these modules.

    Field Type Label Description
    items PBTGTT.TransportEnum repeated Carries max 7 elements of type PBTGTT.TransportEnum

    20.120 genTransportGeneralTestTypes.proto

    20.120.1 RemoteService

    A remote service represents an internet host. It has a hostname which must be in the format of an IPv4 address, a port number, an unsigned integer of 16 bits and a transport type (see transport-enum). It also has a leaf called prime which is of no use at all apart from using it throughout my tests

    Field Type Label Description
    Hostname string optional Specifies the hostname for the service Currently hostnames MUST be in the form of an IPv4 address as we do not support name resolving yet. This is just some BLABLA so I can create a comment for a field in a structure larger than 1 line to see how it gets rendered in the protobuf
    Port uint32 optional Specifies the port where the service can be reached
    Transport TransportEnum optional Specifies the transport protocol to use
    Prime DiscoveredEnumFromInteger optional A field containing a prime number represented as the discovered enum discovered-enum-from-integer

    20.120.2 VarSizeIntegerContainer

    A var sized container carrying unsigned 32 bit integers. The maximum capacity of this container is set to 60000 but this is just a marker as the current implementation of var sized container does no take this limit into account

    Field Type Label Description
    items uint32 repeated Carries max 60000 elements of type uint32

    20.120.3 DiscoveredEnumFromInteger

    A discovered integer enumeration representing the first 8 primes. Please note that 1 is not a prime number.

    Name Number Description
    discovered_enum_from_integer_unknown 0
    discovered_enum_from_integer_2 1
    discovered_enum_from_integer_3 2
    discovered_enum_from_integer_5 3
    discovered_enum_from_integer_7 4
    discovered_enum_from_integer_11 5
    discovered_enum_from_integer_13 6
    discovered_enum_from_integer_17 7
    discovered_enum_from_integer_19 8

    20.120.4 TestEnum

    A first enumeration to test code generation for both messaging and datastore. Enumerations may have a default value. This is indicated by the spacial annotation "default-value". If default value is not specified the first element in the list of enumeration will be chosen

    Name Number Description
    TestEnum_v1 0 The first value for the test enum
    TestEnum_v2 1 The second value for the test enum

    20.120.5 TransportEnum

    Enumeration that specifies the possible transport layers.

    Name Number Description
    Transport_udp 0 UDP transport layer
    Transport_tcp 1 TCP transport layer
    Transport_both 2 UDP or TCP transport layer

    .proto Type Notes C++ Java Python Go C# PHP Ruby
    double double double float float64 double float Float
    float float float float float32 float float Float
    int32 Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint32 instead. int32 int int int32 int integer Bignum or Fixnum (as required)
    int64 Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint64 instead. int64 long int/long int64 long integer/string Bignum
    uint32 Uses variable-length encoding. uint32 int int/long uint32 uint integer Bignum or Fixnum (as required)
    uint64 Uses variable-length encoding. uint64 long int/long uint64 ulong integer/string Bignum or Fixnum (as required)
    sint32 Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int32s. int32 int int int32 int integer Bignum or Fixnum (as required)
    sint64 Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int64s. int64 long int/long int64 long integer/string Bignum
    fixed32 Always four bytes. More efficient than uint32 if values are often greater than 2^28. uint32 int int uint32 uint integer Bignum or Fixnum (as required)
    fixed64 Always eight bytes. More efficient than uint64 if values are often greater than 2^56. uint64 long int/long uint64 ulong integer/string Bignum
    sfixed32 Always four bytes. int32 int int int32 int integer Bignum or Fixnum (as required)
    sfixed64 Always eight bytes. int64 long int/long int64 long integer/string Bignum

    string A string must always contain UTF-8 encoded or 7-bit ASCII text. string String str/unicode string string string String (UTF-8)
    bytes May contain any arbitrary sequence of bytes. string ByteString str []byte ByteString string String (ASCII-8BIT)
